<div class="center">
<h1>About Tigatrapp</h1>
</div>

<p>AtrapaelTigre.com is a citizen science project coordinated by the <a href="http://www.movelab.net">ICREA-Movement Ecology Lab</a> at the <a href="http://www.ceab.csic.es">Centre for Advanced Studies of Blanes</a> (<a href="http://www.csic.es">CSIC</a>).</p>

<p>The project is being implemented in collaboration with CSIC scientific communication officers (Associate Vice President for Scientific Culture, Balearic Islands Delegation, Catalonia Delegation, and Valencia Delegation) and the <a href="http://www.um.es">University of Murcia</a>.</p>

<p>The project is co-financed by the Spanish Foundation for Science and Technology (FECYT) and the Recercaixa research grant program within the framework of the project "Citizen Science: education and research". Bloom is collaborating in the fight against the tiger mosquito by also sponsoring the <a href="http://atrapaeltigre.com">AtrapaelTigre.com</a> project.</p>

<p>The project also has the support of <a href="http://atrapaeltigre.com/web/ca/qui-som/">several other public and private institutions</a>.</p>

<p>All of the photos used in Tigatrapp were provided by <a href="http://www.eritja.com">R. Eritja</a>.</p>

<p>The following icons used in Tigatrapp are derived from the Noun Project: <a href="http://thenounproject.com/term/mosquito/3274/">Mosquito</a> by Monika Ciapala, <a href="http://thenounproject.com/term/water/12145/">Water</a> by Alessandro Suraci, <a href="http://thenounproject.com/term/map/5260/">Map</a> by Jonathan Higley, <a href="http://thenounproject.com/term/images/22772/">Images</a> by Simon Henrotte, <a href="http://thenounproject.com/term/superhero/3302/">Superhero</a> by Simon Child.</p>
